{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3aab6ca3-b310-4b02-9ef4-15424075e84d","content":"In MSTest v4, the first positional parameter of `TestMethodAttribute` became a `[CallerMemberName]` parameter, so your display name string now incorrectly sets the method name instead. The fix is to use the **named `DisplayName` property**.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01BiKhtQjRnKtptQvXqi3PLv","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethod(\"Verify user login works correctly\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Verify user login works correctly\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MzT2ahEKA79SGenv3338FV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethodAttribute(\"Check admin privileges are enforced\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Check admin privileges are enforced\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HJ3X8SyHd1G29LS3P3yWCS","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethod(\"Ensure logout clears session\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Ensure logout clears session\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-adea9916016c47b7bd835f4b682e3953/AuthTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"f2df8974-9b7d-4949-8b85-1b04c139d20f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"In MSTest v4, the `TestMethodAttribute` constructor's first positional parameter became a `[CallerMemberName]` parameter for the test method name, so passing a display name string to the constructor no longer works as intended. The fix is to use the `DisplayName` property instead.\n\nLet me update both files: replace `[TestMethod(\"...\")]` with `[TestMethod]` and add `[DisplayName(\"...\")]` or use the named property syntax.\n\nActually, in MSTest v4, the recommended approach is to use the `DisplayName` property on the attribute: `[TestMethod(DisplayName = \"...\")]`. Let me verify this is the right approach.\n\n\nThe cleanest solution is to use the named `DisplayName` parameter on the attribute, which properly sets the test's display name without conflicting with the constructor's signature change.","outputTokens":713,"requestId":"5C3B:764A5:439BEE:55A637:69F566E1"},"id":"b64166c7-13dc-43fd-b24e-268f3367a418","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:52:28.091Z","parentId":"03a32213-b17a-4c67-8de4-0f7ec4220ec9"}
